definitions.definition: The first year's profits of a Catholic benefice , as traditionally paid directly to the Pope .
The half-year's stipend payable for the vacant half-year after the death of a parish minister, to which his family or nearest of kin have right under an act of 1672.

main_definition: The first year's profits of a Catholic benefice , as traditionally paid directly to the Pope .
